fr:mainmatter.html:div:
Example. 
  Loop unrolling cannot make use of the large distance between dependencies for large k below. 
  for (i = k; i < n; i++)
    a[i] += a[i - k];
  For k = 3, Software pipelining can perform something like
  for (i = 3; i < n; i++)
    a[i - 2] += a[i - 2 - k];
    a[i - 1] += a[i - 1 - k];
    a[i] += a[i - k];
  You can imagine how this becomes more useful as k grows large.

